Really good dvd I have always liked the bill and ted movies. If your a fan of the movies you will like this dvd.

Of course the episodes that are missing are from the totally excellent first season that had actors Keanu Reeves, Alex Winter and George Carlin voice their own characters, while the entire 8 episode "bogus" second season is complete on the second disc. I don't own this, this is just observation from the description. The five episodes that are missing from season one on the first disc are...

"Pocket Watch Full Of Miracles"
"This Babe Ruth "Babe" Is A Dude, Dude"
"Never The Twain Shall Meet"
"A Job, A Job - My Kingdom For A Job"
"A Grimm Story Of An Overdue Book"

I don't see why they couldn't add a third disc and slap on maybe $5 more for the set to make it complete. Oh well. Now if they would release the extremely bogus non non heinous live action series that'd be cool. Excellent! Party on dudes!

Bill & Ted, Beetlejuice, Ghostbusters, Back to the Future, Teen Wolf, somehow there is a generation of cartoons based on movies that weren't always aimed at children. Luckily, the movies were ran on television--sometimes edited. So children often knew the properties well enough to tune into these familiar movie-cartoons.

Bill & Ted was not the best of those movie to cartoon shows. Ghost Busters and Beetlejuice were both better. Bill & Ted fits in with Back to the Future and Teen Wolf.

If you want more from this world of characters, beyond the movies, then the comic books are a better place to explore.
This is an okay nostalgia buy but not as entertaining as you may remember.
